This paper focuses on characterizing kinetic energy for energy harvesting wireless devices, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses developing energy allocation algorithms, which involves mathematical optimization (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions IoT nodes, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses analyzing a motion dataset, which involves data mining and analysis (cs.IR).
